# React Component Conventions

## File Organization

- `components/ui/` — reusable UI primitives (buttons, inputs, modals)
- `components/{domain}/` — domain-specific components (crm, ai, auth, saas, tenant)
- `components/form/` — form components
- `components/tables/` — table components

## Patterns

- **Functional components only** (no class components)
- **PascalCase** filenames matching component name (`AssistantActions.tsx`)
- Use `"use client"` directive only when the component needs browser APIs, state, or effects
- Prefer Server Components for data display
- Extract reusable logic into custom hooks

## Context Providers

Available contexts (import from `@/context/`):
- `SidebarContext` — sidebar open/close state
- `ThemeContext` — light/dark theme
- `WhiteLabelContext` — tenant branding/white-label config

## Styling

- Tailwind CSS v4 utility classes (no `tailwind.config.js` — config is in `globals.css` via `@theme`)
- Use existing design tokens (brand colors, spacing) from the theme
- No inline styles unless dynamically computed
